com.apriori.collections

Class SimpleStringTrie<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.apriori.collections.SimpleStringTrie<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of value stored in the trie
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CompositeTrie<java.lang.CharSequence,java.lang.Character,V>, NavigableCompositeTrie<java.lang.CharSequence,java.lang.Character,V>, java.util.Map<java.lang.CharSequence,V>, java.util.NavigableMap<java.lang.CharSequence,V>, java.util.SortedMap<java.lang.CharSequence,V>

    public abstract class SimpleStringTrie<V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements NavigableCompositeTrie<java.lang.CharSequence,java.lang.Character,V>
    A trie that has String keys. This is nearly the same as using a SortedArrayCompositeTrie<CharSequence, Character, V> but has a couple of useful advantages:
    • This trie supports proper localized sorting of keys via a Collator.
    • This trie is a little more efficient since it uses arrays of primitives (char) instead of the boxed counterpart, Character.
    See Also:
    CompactStringTrie, ArrayMappedStringTrie
